[[File:Thea de Roos - van Rooden.JPG|thumb|Thea de Roos-van Rooden]] '''Th.C.M. (Thea) de Roos-van Rooden ''' (born 27 May 1949 in [[Hillegom]]) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] historian and [[politician]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/2686/Binnenland/article/detail/835941/2007/01/25/Burgemeester-Gaasterl-acirc-n-Sleat-weg.dhtml|title=Burgemeester Gaasterlân-Sleat weg|date=25 January 2007|work=de Volkskrant|language=Dutch|accessdate=28 September 2011}}</ref> for the [[Labour Party (Netherlands)|Labour Party]] (Partij van de Arbeid).
== Biography == She studied history at the [[University of Groningen]] and graduated in 1975. After that she became a history [[teacher]] in [[Haarlem]] and [[Beverwijk]]. In 1978 she was elected as [[councillor]] for the [[municipal council (Netherlands)|city council]] of [[Heemskerk]]. Between 1986 en 1990 she served as an [[alderman]] for this town. In 1990 she became the [[burgemeester|mayor]] of [[Millingen aan de Rijn]].
After resigning in 1997 she was the [[Dijkgraaf (official)|dijkgraaf]] of the [[Water board (The Netherlands)|water board]] "Het Lange Rond" in [[North Holland]]. This board was decommissioned in 2003 after it was incorporated in the new water board "Hoogheemraadschap Hollands Noorderkwartier".
On 1 December 2003 she became the mayor of the [[Friesland|Frisian]] town of [[Gaasterlân-Sleat]]. She resigned in 2007. In 2009 she was elected as a member of the water board "Hoogheemraadschap Rijnland".
Besides her educational and political activities she published several books, most of them on local history.
