{{Infobox journal | title = Transactions of the American Philological Association | cover = Transactions of the american philological association.gif | editor = Craig Gibson | discipline = [[Classics]], [[philology]] | abbreviation = Trans. Am. Philol. Assoc. | publisher = [[Johns Hopkins University Press]] | country = United States | frequency = Biannually | history = 1869-present | openaccess = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.press.jhu.edu/journals/transactions_of_the_american_philological_association/ | link1 = http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/transactions_of_the_american_philological_association/ | link1-name = Online access at [[Project MUSE]] | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 3131421 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0360-5949 | eISSN = 1533-0699 }} '''''Transactions of the American Philological Association''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] established in 1869 and the official publication of the [[American Philological Association]]. It covers the history, culture, and language of [[Ancient Greece|ancient Greek]] and [[Ancient Rome|Roman]] societies. The journal is published biannually by the [[Johns Hopkins University Press]].
